      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EXTRA PINEAPPLE (8) looks close to win after hitting the frame last run (22.43) at this track in a Grade 4/5. Has first look at box 8 this time. Has never been out of the money in four starts this distance. Rates highly and will give a great sight. BART'S CHANCE (7) was game in defeat at the latest run, finishing second and beaten a nose (22.58) behind TERRITORY MAN at this track. Overdue and is among the main hopes. SO NAIVE (1) stuck on well last time to finish a neck back in third (22.59) at this track in a Grade 5 /MDN over 383m. Expected to be in this for a long way. TERRITORY GIRL (2) was well supported last time but could only manage second (18.76), beaten a nose. Well-placed to take this out.",
